## Tables Hibernate will auto-create

| Table | Columns |
|---|---|
| `volunteer_opportunities` | All entity fields |
| `volunteer_opportunity_skills` | `opportunity_id`, `skill` (one row per skill) |

## API quick reference

| Method | URL | Description |
|---|---|---|
| POST | `/api/v1/volunteer-opportunities` | Submit form (your `handleSubmit`) |
| GET | `/api/v1/volunteer-opportunities/{id}` | Get one |
| GET | `/api/v1/volunteer-opportunities?category=&location=` | Search active |
| GET | `/api/v1/volunteer-opportunities/campaign/{id}` | By campaign |
| PUT | `/api/v1/volunteer-opportunities/{id}` | Update |
| PATCH | `/api/v1/volunteer-opportunities/{id}/status?status=ACTIVE` | Admin approve |
| DELETE | `/api/v1/volunteer-opportunities/{id}` | Delete |
